GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 3
HOUSE BILL 616
Committee Substitute Favorable 4/29/25
Third Edition Engrossed 5/7/25
Short Title: Megasites/Selectsites Program Revisions. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
April 1, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MODIFY THE MEGASITES AND SELECTSITES READINESS PROGRAMS.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1.(a) Section 11.11 of S.L. 2022-74, as amended by Section 11.11 of S.L.
5 2023-134, reads as rewritten:
6 "SECTION 11.11.(a) Purpose. – It is in the best economic and developmental interests of
7 the State to support the development of megasites to ensure the State's ongoing competitiveness
8 for major manufacturing opportunities, including, but not limited to, the aerospace, automotive,
9 clean energy, food processing, semiconductor, and life science industries. The purpose of this
10 section is to establish a competitive grant program serving to do the following:
11 (1) Identify and evaluate up to seven megasites for preferred development and
12 marketing.
13 (2) Assist local governments or a partnership of local governments in the
14 acquisition of a newly identified or existing megasite.
15 (3) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to analyze,
16 plan, install, or upgrade public infrastructure, including publicly owned water,
17 gas, and sewer systems, transportation infrastructure, and the electrical utility
18 lines electric infrastructure necessary to meet the needs of prospective
19 employers for megasites.
20 (4) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to fund
21 on-site preparation, including clearing, grading, or other related expenses for
22 megasites.
23 (4a) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments in
24 conducting due diligence, including, but not limited to, the following: site
25 characteristics, preliminary engineering reports for water and wastewater
26 provision to the site, assessments related to road and highway infrastructure
27 to serve the site, and other assessments as needed.
28 (5) Facilitate coordination between the economic development entities, the North
29 Carolina Department of Environmental Quality, and the North Carolina
30 Department of Transportation to expedite needs related to timely site
31 development.
32 …
33 "SECTION 11.11.(c) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
34 …
