General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (4) Government partnership. – Either (i) a North Carolina nonprofit entity that is
2 tax exempt under section 501(c)(3) or 501(c)(12) of the Internal Revenue
3 Code in partnership with one or more local governments or (ii) a group of
4 local governments.
5 …
6 "SECTION 11.11.(d) Allocation. – EDPNC shall allocate monies in the Fund on the
7 following basis:
8 …
9 (2) All other funds appropriated to the Fund for local government grants for the
10 acquisition of megasites determined pursuant to subdivision (1) of this
11 subsection. purposes described in subsection (a) of this section. A grant for
12 the acquisition of a megasite is limited to eighty-five percent (85%) of the
13 lesser of the property's purchase price or tax value. The percentage actually
14 provided in the grant shall be determined by EDPNC based on total
15 development needs for the megasite, prior investment in the megasite by one
16 or more local governments, the ability of one or more local governments to
17 invest in the megasite, and the ability and level of participation promised by
18 the local government in exchange for a grant from the Fund. Monies may only
19 be granted for, and used to acquire, a megasite for which (i) one or more local
20 governments have a binding option or offer to purchase and (ii) all basic due
21 diligence must be complete, including, but not limited to, boundary surveys,
22 title searches, State Historic Preservation Office reviews, and wetlands
23 delineation.
24 …
25 "SECTION 11.11.(f) Agreements Required. – Monies may be disbursed from the Fund
26 previously appropriated for the Megasite Readiness Program shall be transferred in full to
27 EDPNC when this act becomes law. Funds subsequently appropriated for the Program shall be
28 transferred in full to EDPNC once such an act becomes law. EDPNC may use funds only in
29 accordance with agreements that are (i) entered into between EDPNC and a local government or
30 a government partnership and (ii) approved by the Economic Investment Committee established
31 pursuant to G.S. 143B-437.54. The agreement must include all of the performance criteria,
32 remedies, and other safeguards required to secure the assistance provided to ready the megasite
33 for a major employer and must require EDPNC to recapture a proportionate amount of assistance
34 provided under this section for failure by a local government or government partnership to meet
35 and maintain the megasite for availability for the purposes for which the assistance was provided.
36 …."
37 SECTION 1.(b) Section 11.12 of S.L. 2023-134 reads as rewritten:
38 "SECTION 11.12.(a) Funds appropriated by Section 11.4 11.4(d)(1) of S.L. 2022-74 to the
39 Department of Commerce (Department) and allocated to the nonprofit corporation with which
40 the Department contracts pursuant to G.S. 143B-431.01(b) that remain unspent as of June 30,
41 2023, April 1, 2025, shall be transferred to the North Carolina Selectsite Fund established in
42 subsection (c) of this section to be used for purposes consistent with subdivision (e)(1) of this
43 section. Of the funds appropriated from the Economic Development Project Reserve established
44 in Section 2.2 of this act to the Department to be allocated to the nonprofit corporation with which
45 the Department contracts pursuant to G.S. 143B-431.01(b), the sum of ten million dollars
46 ($10,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2024-2025 fiscal year shall be used to support local
47 governments or a partnership of local governments in conducting due diligence as described in
48 subdivision for the purposes described in subdivisions (b)(2), (b)(3), (b)(4), and (b)(5) of this
49 section.
50 "SECTION 11.12.(b) Purpose. – It is in the best economic and developmental interests of
51 the State to support the development of selectsites to ensure the State's ongoing competitiveness
