1 for major manufacturing opportunities, including, but not limited to, the aerospace, automotive,
2 clean energy, food processing, semiconductor, and life science industries. The purpose of this
3 section is to establish a competitive grant program serving to do the following:
4 (1) Identify and evaluate up to 15 20 selectsites of less than 1,000 acres for
5 preferred development and marketing.
6 (2) Assist local governments or a partnership of local governments in the
7 acquisition of a newly identified or existing selectsite.
8 (3) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to analyze,
9 plan, install, or upgrade public infrastructure, including publicly owned water,
10 gas, and sewer systems; transportation infrastructure; and the electrical utility
11 lines electric infrastructure necessary to meet the needs of prospective
12 employers for selectsites.
13 (4) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments to fund
14 on-site preparation, including clearing, grading, or other related expenses for
15 selectsites.
16 (5) Support local governments or a partnership of local governments in
17 conducting due diligence, including, but not limited to, the following: site
18 characteristics, preliminary engineering reports for water and wastewater
19 provision to the site, assessments related to road and highway infrastructure
20 to serve the site, and other assessments as needed.
21 (6) Facilitate coordination between the economic development entities and the
22 North Carolina Department of Environmental Quality and the North Carolina
23 Department of Transportation to expedite needs related to timely site
24 development.
25 …
26 "SECTION 11.12.(e) Allocation. – EDPNC shall allocate monies in the Fund on the
27 following basis:
28 (1) Unspent funds transferred pursuant to subsection (a) of this section shall be
29 used for engaging a national site selection firm through a competitive bid
30 process to produce a report identifying and evaluating 15 selectsites for
31 preferred development and marketing, of which seven must be less than 500
32 acres and of which an additional two must be less than 100 acres. Further
33 unspent funds transferred pursuant to subsection (a) of this section shall be
34 used for engaging a national site selection firm through a competitive bid
35 process to produce a supplemental report identifying and evaluating up to five,
36 and no less than three, additional selectsites from the initial disaster declared
37 counties resulting from Tropical Storm Helene.
38 (2) Funds appropriated to the Fund for local government grants shall be allocated
39 for the purposes outlined in subdivisions (b)(2), (b)(3), (b)(4), and (b)(5) of
40 this section for selectsites determined pursuant to subdivision (1) of this
41 subsection. EDPNC shall prioritize local government grants that have the
42 greatest potential to reduce the time for site readiness and reduce the risk of
43 unforeseen conditions that could affect the site viability for advanced
44 manufacturing projects. EDPNC shall base the grant amount on total
45 development needs for the selectsite, prior investment in the selectsite by one
46 or more local governments, the ability of one or more local governments to
47 invest in the selectsite, and the ability and level of participation promised by
48 the local government in exchange for a grant from the Fund. Monies may only
49 be granted for, and used to acquire, a selectsite for which (i) one or more local
50 governments have a binding option or offer to purchase and (ii) all basic due
51 diligence has been completed, including, but not limited to, boundary surveys,
