1 title searches, State Historic Preservation Office reviews, and wetlands
2 delineation.
3 (3) Of the monies available in the fund, no more than $150,000 shall be used
4 biennially for engaging a national site selection firm through a competitive
5 bid process to produce a report identifying and evaluating seven new
6 selectsites for preferred development and marketing, of which three must be
7 less than 500 acres and of which an additional two must be less than 100 acres.
8 Geographic diversity must be a priority consideration in the identification of
9 new sites beginning with the report due in 2026.
10 …
11 "SECTION 11.12.(g) Agreements Required. – Monies may be disbursed from the Fund
12 previously appropriated for the Selectsite Readiness Program shall be transferred in full to
13 EDPNC when this act becomes law. Funds subsequently appropriated for the Program shall be
14 transferred in full to EDPNC once such an act becomes law. EDPNC may use funds only in
15 accordance with agreements entered into between EDPNC and a local government or a
16 government partnership. The agreement must include all of the performance criteria, remedies,
17 and other safeguards required to secure the assistance provided to ready the selectsite for a major
18 employer and must require EDPNC to recapture a proportionate amount of assistance provided
19 under this section for failure by a local government or government partnership to meet and
20 maintain the selectsite for availability for the purposes for which the assistance was provided.
21 …."
22 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
